---
title: DataCite - Search
---

<header class="image-bg-fixed-height-small">
  <div class="jumbotron">
    <h1>
      Search
    </h1>
  </div>
</header>

<section>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-9 section-content">
        <h1>service description</h1>
        <p>
          DataCite gathers metadata for each DOI assigned to an object. The
          metadata is used  for a large index of research data that can be
          queried directly to find data, obtain stats and explore connections.
          All the metadata is free to access and review.
        </p>
        <p>
          To showcase and expose the metadata gathered, DataCite provides an
          integrated search interface, where it is possible to search, filter
          and extract all the details from a collection of millions of records.
        </p>
        <p>
          This interface complements the OAI-PMH service, providing an
          actionable end-point to query DataCite's metadata collection.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-3 bg-primary sidebox">
        <h1>access details</h1>
        <ul>
          <li> Accessible through:
            <br /> <i class="fa fa-external-link"></i>
            <%= link_to 'http://search.datacite.org',
            'http://search.datacite.org' %>
          <li>
            Intended users:
            <ul>
              <li>- DataCite members
                <br />- Users and integrators
                <br />- Community
            </ul>
          <li> Availability:
            <br /> <i class="fa fa-external-link"></i>
            <%= link_to 'http://status.datacite.org',
            'http://status.datacite.org' %>
          <li> User documentation:
            <br /> <i class="fa fa-external-link"></i>
            <%= link_to 'http://support.datacite.org',
            'https://support.datacite.org/docs/datacite-search-user-documentation' %>
        </ul>
        <h1>learn more</h1>
        <ul>
          <li>DataCite Metadata Schema:
            <br /> <i class="fa fa-external-link"></i>
            <%= link_to 'http://schema.datacite.org',
            'http://schema.datacite.org' %>
          <li>DataCite blog:
            <br /> <i class="fa fa-external-link"></i>
            <%= link_to 'http://blog.datacite.org/from...',
            'http://blog.datacite.org/from-pilot-to-service/' %>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>